body:
@Guson, you cannot just copy nunit.engine.api.dll into the old addins directory of 2.6.x. You must use a full install of v3 of nunit-console including the new engine and update your batch file accordingly.

If you want it to work with your batch file, you will need to uninstall 2.6.3 or remove it from your path, install v3 of the console and add it to your path.

For point 2, / will work for command line parameters on Windows. -- is better because it is cross platform.
